reviews:
The services were amazing.
You would receive many different kinds of bread (tasty) for your breakfast.
The beds were comfortable and they had some special duvets and bed sheets which keeps you cool in hot summers- that I thought great.

The overall hotel isn’t big but it is located only 5 mins or less away from the Louvre museum.

Hotel L'Empire is a gem of a find! Location is perfect - around the corner from the Louvre, walking distance to Notre Dame/Sainte Chapelle/Conciergeries. Also very near the (new) Les Halles market and the Marais. I stayed for 4 nights and my room, on the top floor (there is an elevator), was quiet and good-sized, with both a bathtub with shower and a walk-in shower stall. The hotel has clearly been renovated recently. Breakfast was generous and delicious. The staff was extremely welcoming, friendly and helpful, and spoke multiple languages. A bonus was the shuttle service to/from the airport that they arranged. I will definitely stay here again. Highly recommended.

My adult sons and I absolutely enjoyed staying at the L’Empire Hotel. Our rooms were clean and lovely. I especially liked the accessible room where I was able to use my wheelchair/walker easily. We also enjoyed the breakfast each morning. The shuttle to and from the airport was great. Also, the front desk personnel were helpful and positive, and their communication emails before we came were very useful. Showers had hot water and WIFI worked well. I would recommend this hotel to anyone who wants a good location and great service! Thank you to their entire staff!

My wife, or 12 yo, and I just returned from 9 days staying at L’Empire Paris. It was wonderful. I booked a small suite in this boutique hotel, since we did not want to be on top of each other, especially given how small hotel rooms tend to be in Paris. The decor was very modern, and not ostentatious. While the hotel was not the lap of luxury, the front desk staff were STELLAR. We were made to feel so incredibly welcomed when finally arrived, after 2 hours getting through CDG. They provided us with recommendations, made last-minute reservations for us, and booked a trip for us. Breakfast was lovely; very French: croissants and French bread, cafe au lait, hot chocolate for our daughter, fresh squeezed orange juice, charcuterie, cheese, smoked salmon, cereal, sausage, and did I mention cheese? The hotel was also very centrally located, close to two metro stations, off of Rue de Rivoli, but on a quiet street. Restaurants abounded. If you are looking for an incredibly friendly, comfortable, and centrally located hotel, look no further!

Great centrally located hotel close to the Louvre and many great restaurants. We walked everywhere. Staff were super friendly and helpful. Room was bigger than we expected and it was well appointed, comfortable and quiet. Wine and cheese store right next door was a bonus. Great first stop on our French vacation.

Dear my friends and to my host the employees at L’Empire, Paris -

I recently stayed at your bed and breakfast. I very much enjoyed your accommodation and especially enjoyed meeting the hotel staff during my brief visit. All of the employees were so very kind and helpful. The front desk individuals, the breakfast staff, and the room service help were all a delight !

Now I am back in USA I am already recommending your establishment to future travelers to Paris and yes, you can count me in as a return visitor.

Thank you so much !

We had superior double room on the top floor, which was nice. Even could see the top of the eiffel tower.
Location is very good, short walk to Louvre & Metro.
Rooms / Hotel are clean and tidy.
Plumbing could be a little noisy but not disturbing.
Staff were excellent.

L’Empire Hotel
Very nice hotel located within easy walking distance to the Louvre. Our room was very stylish with plenty of room in which to move about. Lots of power outlets available in the room. There was a desk. The bathroom was small. Counter space around the vessel sink was adequate. The shower was powerful, but with no shower curtain or door a great deal of water splashed out onto the bathroom floor, completely soaking the supplied bath mat and an additional towel we placed there. As there is no exhaust fan the passive vent was unable to keep up with the steam in the bathroom. They have a shaving mirror but the light in the bathroom was too dim to use it for makeup. The breakfast buffet looked quite extensive but we had to leave too early to try it. Staff was friendly and helpful.

The room was big and great. It was very clean. Personnel very polite and breakfast was nice although it could have more variety. Location fantastic. It didn't have any view but i didn't mind. It was very quiet. My daughters loved it. I would stay again!!!

This was our fourth trip to Paris, and the first time to stay at the Hotel L’Empire. I can say without reservation that should we travel again to this great city; this will be our home base.

The rooms have a quintessential Parisian feel while being very modern and immaculately clean. The included breakfast buffet includes some American favorites such as scrambled eggs and (delicious) sausage as well as typically French selections accompanied by fresh juice and excellent coffee, and all is included in the room price.

While all the physical aspects and amenities sparkle, the professionalism of the staff rises above all else. Every single staff member proved to be intent on a pleasurable stay for our group. We found them to be above and beyond in accommodating our needs and questions, and particularly helpful in securing transportation during the protests and Metro strike strike.

The location in the 1st arronisment was just perfect, with the Louvre, Muse D’Orsay, Notre Dame, the Concierge and the Forum at Les Halles all within very reasonable walking distance. Chatelet station is just a few blocks away, no more than a five-minute stroll. In previous visits we have stayed near the Champs-Élysées, in the Marias and Montmartre—the Hotel L’Empire is in by far the best location for us.

Merci de tout coeur to all the team at Hotel L’Empire!

The hotel was absolutely beautiful and the rooms were nice and clean and spacious. We had the buffet breakfast which was fantastic the staff were really helpful and friendly.
So many restaurants close by and the train station.
We highly recommend this hotel

Perfect, unless you are senstive to some witty sarcasm from the staff, L'Empire is our now favourite place to stay whilst in Paris. Well located near Pont Neuf, Samaritaine, and the Louvre, it is within easy walking distance of many major sites with easy access from CDG bia Chatelet-les-Halles RER B.

Breakfast was much more than a simple continental fare. Delicious offerings with amazing bread, naturally, fresh-squeezed orange juice, and a wide range of typical breakfast choices. Superb!

Our room was large and not just by Parisian standards. We later stayed at the Marriott Champs Elysees this trip and yet L'Empire was a superior experience.

The staff is what made this experience so amazing. Desk staff were helpful and considerate; the breakfast and bar staff were attentive; but most of all, being greeted by Sophie (?) was a memorable welcome. She is truly the highlight of our Christmas stay at L'Empire!

From the minute we walked in Antonio and Max greeted us with a smile and made our check in process easy. They answered all our questions and were super helpful. The rooms were clean and well appointed. The location is great, a very short walk to the Louvre, and most sites are within a 30-40 minute walk. We used Uber for most of our transportation needs, but the staff is helpful in getting you a taxi if you choose. I highly recommend L Empire Paris.

Merci, Merci, Merci! Thank you to Sonia, Max and the entire team! We had the most pleasant stay at Hotel L’Empire Paris.

From the moment we arrived in the middle of the night we were greeted with compassion and kindness. Not only did we receive assistance with our lost baggage (which was waiting for us in our room when we arrived at the hotel one evening), they were apologetic and ultimately tracked down my daughter’s doll when it was accidentally taken by housekeeping with the sheets! Sonia also provided the best restaurant recommendations! The room was gorgeous, comfortable and able to appropriately accommodate our family of five! The breakfast was great and the staff were all polite and pleasant.

Thank you to the Hotel L’Empire Paris! We will highly recommend you to friends and family. We look forward to staying with you again the next time we are in Paris!

The Guberman Family

Not a 4 Star Hotel. Good location, nice staff and big rooms but very dated, in need of painting/cleaning and poor amenities. Bad/dumb TV with lousy cable and no coffee maker. Expensive breakfast is not worth the price.

had a wonderful seven days in Paris and
part of that was because the L’Empire staff was so friendly and helpful. Everyone was helpful but especially Sonia… she was truly amazing and a credit to the hotel .

I will definitely stay at L’Empire on my next visit
in 2023. There is no reason to look for another hotel since the accommodations , staff and location are
just a few of the reasons to choose L’Empire.
The perfect spot to start any walk in Central Paris.

Thank you for your hospitality. It made my stay
the best yet.

Faye Sheffield

Firstly, if they tell you you are going to be upgraded to a larger room in the basement, refuse!!! We were told it would be quiet. We were woken by noise in the corridor (the room is just next to the spa and some type of staff service area) at 4 or 5am and it went on for ages. Other reviews we have since read said the same. They told us it looked out into the garden - again, don’t be fooled. It’s an outside space but definitely not a garden! The basement is dark and pretty unappealing all in all. We complained the next morning and they promptly moved us to a better room on the 3rd floor. Other things to mention. The safe in the basement room did not work. We asked them to fix it. They said they’d send someone. It still didn’t work. The pillows were awful in the basement room. As if someone had put them in a washing machine and they’d come out with the insides all chewed up. The towels are thin. The rooms themselves feel quite stark - they need a rug or something to make them feel more welcoming.
On the plus side, it’s a great location. The front desk was very helpful when we asked to change rooms and the staff were generally friendly. The breakfast was good but I wouldn’t stay again unfortunately as our experience was not a great one. I’ve stayed in many hotels in Paris over the last 30 years and unfortunately this for me is at the bottom end. I’m sorry to write this as I very rarely write anything negative but I hope it might be helpful both to the hotel and other future guests.

My friends and I stayed at the L’Empire Paris Hotel for 4 days prior to and 3 days after a river cruise. The rooms were great and the location was wonderful. Our reservations included breakfast, which was very good. What made this Hôtel memorable was the staff. Everyone was friendly, helpful, and did everything possible to make our Paris experience awesome. Sonya (manager) in particular went out of her way to make us all feel at home. If I’m ever fortunate enough to visit Paris again I will definitely stay at L’Empire.

We stayed at the L'Empire in Paris in mid-October. Good location near public transportation, but off the busy roads. The staff (especially in the kitchen/bar/breakfast) were incredibly nice and helpful. The front desk staff were hit-and-miss. The room was clean and comfortable, although we had trouble figuring out the light switches -- but that is part of the charm! Our room faced the courtyard, so it was quiet and peaceful. Our stay gets only four stars due to a few unusual items -- the room coffee maker was dirty and moldy, our room needed a bigger closet or more wall hooks for hanging wet coats, and the HVAC system underpowered. But that is typical for many boutique hotels. So, would I go back? Maybe. Nice enough, but we may try a different hotel next time.

Such a nice hotel! We actually booked at L’Empire in 2020, but were unable to travel due to the pandemic. So I contacted them in 2022 to ask if they could give us a discount, based on our expired, non-refundable booking. They generously credited our entire booking! The staff is very nice, the location is really ideal, and the room was very comfortable and well-thought-out, making great use of the space without feeling cramped. Enjoyed our stay a lot!

After reading the website we decided on the Le Empire Hotel as it looked very impressive. Whilst the staff are very friendly and helpful, the hotel was in the main disappointing. We booked a room with a terrace and jacuzzi, thinking this would be a great extra and worthwhile paying extra for, however in reality the terrace was overlooked on all sides by adjoining flats with little or no sunlight, the chairs had no cushions and the bean bags were mouldy and covered in bird droppings. There were no chairs for the random dirty table outside either. The jacuzzi smelt of mould so was not used at all which was again a big disappointment. The room was comfortable although getting in the door was very problematical as the card key always took at least 15-20 Insertions before it would work, we even changed cards and the new one was no better. Breakfast was okay, but the selection was limited. The toaster was very basic and took forever to heat up, it also only catered for 4 slices a time. On Sunday the bread ran out so several people were not able to have toast. The website stated a restaurant but the menu was for room service and we never saw anyone eating at lunch or dinner. Location was great, but expectations were not met. As I say good staff but the rest missed the mark unfortunately.

The room was clean and spacious. The staff were very accommodating. Nicolai and Joao really made my time at the hotel fun. The location of the hotel made it easy for sight seeing and close to a plethora of restaurants and shops.

This wonderful little hotel is perfectly located for train lines, museums, shopping and food. The room was nice and clean, noise was not too bad and breakfast was OK. We had a lovely time, a big thank you to the staff who made the stay a pleasure.

L'Empire Paris has wonderful customer care!!! The rooms are so clean and wonderfully kept.
The staff at L'Empire Paris are amazing and extremely helpful.
This hotel is perfectly situated. It has so many restaurants and eating places which are within reach.
We had such a great time, will definitely come back.

The location of the Hotel is perfect! In walking distance from the Louvre or les Halles. METRO is also not far. You find lots of nice restaurants and shopping possibilities. Breakfast is great and the people / Service excellent.

The location is perfect – a walking distance from many city attractions, supermarkets, shops, restaurants and more.
Also close to several metro stations and bus stops, in case you need to use public transport.
The staff was very hospitable and friendly. Breakfast was good with a decent variety.

The main issue I found – the hotel is not accessible by car. I didn't find any mention of that in the reviews I read, and had to find out the hard way.
Apparently, two yeas ago, the city of Paris closed Rivoli street (the main road leading to the hotel) to car traffic except for taxis, buses and emergency vehicles.
We arrived with a driver from a private company, which could not access the hotel location, so we had to get out and walk to the hotel for about 200 meters. Not a disaster, but certainly not fun with luggage.
Also, a minor nuisance – there were no clothes hangers in the shower in the room I stayed.

I stayed alone at the hotel from 28/09 and 06/10. Quiet and well-sanitized room, honest breakfast without many options, low quality cold cuts and nothing new during the stay. However, excellent location. The high point of the hotel is the friendliness and cordiality of the attendants at the reception. Highlighting the professionalism, promptness and dynamism of Miss Sonia and Mr João. These certainly make the difference that brings us back!

When in Paris for the weekend and visiting the Louvre, this is our favorite place to stay. We've stayed at L'Empire Paris twice and had a wonderful stay both times. The beds are extremely comfortable, everything is clean, the staff (especially Sonia!!) are friendly, helpful and fun to talk with. I would recommend this hotel to any of my friends and family, and when I'm in the neighborhood, this is my place to stay. If there was one downside, it would be that I have to send my partner to get coffee for me because we can't make it in the room. But truly, that's the only minus in their great amount of checkmarks.

A long weekend in Paris, at the start of autumn. The hotel is very well located, only a short walk from several Metro stops, and the river Seine, so it provided an ideal base for our weekend. The breakfast is good and the rooms are comfortable, with coffee machines and safes, and a good bathroom. The best facet of the hotel however is the staff, particularly on the front desk - they were very helpful, very friendly and turned this review into a 5 star review !

Our handicap room much larger than many more expensive in Paris, and very wheelchair friendly. Staff very polite, quick to deal with any requests, or provide a suggestion or tourist tip. Louvre and Les Halles a short stroll away, and Notre Dame, d'Orsay, and lots more not much further. At least 20 restaurants within a couple blocks, we tried something different every meal (except we soon found a favorite bakery nearby that supplied us with many baguettes and desserts). When and if we return to Paris, we will also return to L'Empire.

My husband and I are currently vacationing in Spain with our daughter and her husband. We all reside in British Columbia, Canada. My son-in-law reserved at L’Empire way in advance, well before leaving Canada on September 13. Two days before anticipated check-in on October 1, he received an email from L’Empire saying his credit card payment did not go through and so the reservation would be canceled. He was unsuccessful phoning the hotel to sort out this problem so sent emails requesting they call or email him to confirm credit card details. No reply. This morning I called and spoke, in French, to the front desk employee who gave me that « I’ll have to speak to my manager runaround » . Hours later, no contact. I phoned again saying I was about to write a negative review on Trip Advisor, which I have now done.

This hotel is located very close to many of the major sites. Within one block of the river made it very nice and easy to go for walks every day. Close to shopping and food.

The hotel staff were very friendly and went out of their way to be sure everything was perfect.

Absolutely the number one staff we have worked with in our many years of travel. The rooms are clean
and very comfortable.. The location is perfect. The number one asset is their most dedicated staff to
Customer service. Unbelievable! Gave exceptional professional and personal service and stepped up beyond expectations to help when needed. We wanted to pack this team up and bring them home with us to North Carolina .

Great location, kindly staff, comfortable room, super clean, good breakfast. Recommend hotel to stay in Paris, beside the Louvre, near Sena river, you can walk to many different interesting touristic places. If you are traveling by car, have a 3 minutes secure parking from the hotel.

Wow , great service , everybody goes out of their way to help you . The reception staff top notch ! The server the best ! Even the cleaning staff are great. The location is great , steps away from metro and the Louvre Museum . Will come back for sure .

We had amazing stay. Special thanks to Sonia and the team of staff that made our visit so special!

The hotel is in great location, a few minutes walk to the Louvre but on a quiet street. It is very clean, fresh and modern with great air conditioning. The delicious toffees in the room were a nice touch.

The public carpark in the next street is a one minute walk and takes cars over 2m without needing to book. For a car/van over 2m it costs euro 80 for 24hrs but we'll worth it for the convenience.

We are a family of 5 and our daughter is in a wheelchair. Travel can be stressful but thanks to Sonia for going the extra mile, making sure we had a taxis with a ramp and coming out to talk to the driver etc (and the staff at the Eiffel Tower/Louvre, were we didn't have to queue) the whole family has very enjoyable stay in Paris.

modern structure and close to several services. good room cleaning. spacious rooms divided into two areas. good breakfast. all the receptionists are friendly and prepared for any request of information

Had a very pleasant stay with a family group of 3. Room is big and very clean. Location is central but quiet. Hat off to front desk Sonia and Max for going extra miles helping us navigate the PCR test and arranging last minute transportation.
Will definitely recommend this hotel to friends and will stay here again when come visit Paris.

Wow - this place went above and beyond our expectations. First, the staff was so attentive! Always somebody at the desk, always willing to help us with either directions, or head to the bar for water bottle refill, or answer any questions about where to go or how to get there. Room was always tidy. The place - GREAT breakfast, GREAT A/C, perfect location and very clean. Not one to stay at the same place twice, I will make an exception and definitely want to stay here again. We were a party of 5 (odd number for Europe) but a king bed for the parents, hide a bed was great for our 2 girls (16 and 21) and the roll away worked great for our 21 year old boy. Thank you L'Empire!!! You made our trip the best!

We stayed at the hotel for 5 days . The hotel was perfect, clean, great location near the louver, large and spacious rooms and amazing staff .highly recommend . Next time in Paris we will come back again

We, a famliy of 5, were stranded in Paris late in the evening as we had been scammed on a reservation through booking. The staff at L`Empire quickly arranged a lovely room big enough for us when I called them in a crisis. I also asked if they could help us find accomodation for the following two nights as they were fully booked. When we got to the hotel the kind man at reception had already found us accomodation and called ahead to find exact information and prices. He also made the reservation for us.

The room was tasteful, clean and beds were very comfortable. Perfect location for city walks and seeing the sights. We also loved the breakfast!

I will definately return to L´Empire for my next Paris trip!

You MUST stay at this hotel when making a trip to Paris!
Our trip started when we came in on July 14th. Being Bastille Day, I think the hotel may have been short-staffed and our room was not ready, but Sonia and the rest of the staff turned a negative into a positive. They were soooo kind and friendly, took our bags, gave us a place to rest, and recommended a perfect place to get a quick bite to eat. Now, normally you would expect to get directions to this place to eat, but no, Sonia actually walked us down the road to the restaurant! How dedicated!
For the remainder of our trip, anything we needed and asked for we had immediately like we were kings and queens!
Today, our last day, they held our bags at no cost for us to get in a few more hours of sightseeing before leaving for the airport and even offered us an umbrella to use because of the bit of rain coming down.
In short, if you want to be treated like kings and queens, stay at the L’Empire Hotel right in the heart of beautiful Paris!

Delightful Boutique hotel... in a neighborhood filled with a mix of local residents. A basic but very clean & comfortable room., Front desk staff was very friendly and helpful with excellent English... something you don't find everywhere in ParisWe will return to this property! Only problem was the bathtub/shower was a "high walled/deep step down" tub (and no safety hand-rails) which is difficult for older folks like us.

Would like them to illuminate the front face of the hotel... it would make it less gloomy and more inviting. Also IN THE FRONT LOBBY... a coffee pot in the morning for a "grab & go", and a "iced water station" in the afternoon would be a good move!

The location is perfect. The hotel is small and easy to manage, but it's the staff and service that make it great. Easy to get a cab. Walking distance from the Louvre. Great cafes close by. Close to shopping.

Everything was ideal. The Staff, the room and The location were all exceptional. Everyone was very friendly and we had no problem communicating since we do not speak French. They gave us great recommendations for restaurants. We will stay here again.

This hotel is wonderfully located and has staff that go above and beyond to help you enjoy your stay in Paris. The hotel is a quick walk to the Louvre and the Siene. There are a ton of bistros and restaurants near by. The rooms are spacious and well cleaned. But the real star of the hotel is the staff that runs. They really work to make your stay comfortable. The staff was so accommodating with my daughter and I. I highly recommend this hotel.

This is a boutique hotel in a great location . Out the door are restaurant options , shopping options are minutes away ! Museums are minutes away. The front desk staff are young , friendly & helpful . The breakfast is fabulous. The room is clean, good bedding . We were a family of 4 children and three adults . We had adjoining rooms . And a separate room . We Highly recommend this hotel .

Absolutely excellent. The staff were great. Very helpful in English as well. Great service. Great location. Great staff from the front desk to the wait staff for breakfast. Very helpful with directions and how to use the metro. We found our place. Next and all times we will stay at L'Empire. Bar none the best and great location for walking and using the Metro to get to all the locations.

Great location in 1er with lots of bistros and boulangeries nearby, which is convenient for a quick meal for those jet lagged. Louvre is just minutes away, and shopping malls are easy to get to. Friendly staff is a plus, and convenient alcohol/breakfast bar in the hotel.

One thing to note, however, is that it may be a bit difficult to catch an Uber to the hotel from other Arrondissements due to heavy traffic in 1er. Leaving the hotel to other attraction sites is not an issue. Having said that, a lot of attraction sites are in walking distance.

Excellent service, very clean rooms and exceptional location! Very friendly and responsible staff.
We really enjoyed continental breakfast buffet!
Highly recommend!
It was 2 minutes walk to Louvre museum. Great and variety of restaurants in walking distance.

Our first time in Paris, and this hotel is really worth coming back to. The room was big, clean, had a mini bar, safe, robes, curtains to block the sun, a big tv and a really good bed. On the negative side there were not much to look at on the telly because of the french channels, but what can you expect in France.

The most negative thing about this hotel was the noises that you could hear from the other rooms...

The staff are sooo good. They speak very good english and are so helpful and always smiling. The breakfast was good also. In terms of throwing away food, I hope they recycle the croissants that we get at the table and dont eat because we got a big box every day and there was to many for us to eat.

You live right next to the metro, the rer to take to the airport, the louvre and a 4 km walk to the eiffeltower. Just to blocks down you can rent bicicyles for just 8 euros a day.

Love this hotel!

This was our first time in Paris and I have to say our stay here made it 10x better. The hotel staff was outstanding in helping us when we needed it unlike others in the city that we encountered. We got steered in the wrong direction many times by many people outside of our hotel. Max and Peter went above and beyond to make sure we had everything we needed and knew our way around. They and all the hotel staff were always available to help. The day of checkout our Uber ride to the airport cancelled on us very last minute and we couldn’t secure a ride in time. We had no choice but to catch the train to the airport. Max was kind enough to show us to the train station so we would not get lost. We got so lucky that he did this for us. We can’t stress enough the difference this made to us. We were able to get to the airport with enough time to pass through security and customs. The hospitality here was the reason our first time in Paris was amazing. Our room was spacious, clean, had AC, and the bed was super comfy. We could not ask for a better place to stay. We will definitely be back!

The room was large and comfortable and generally well appointed. The location is excellent. This was the first time we stayed on the right bank and we were very glad that we did. Hotel staff were attentive and helpful at all times. Breakfast was excellent. One complaint worth mentioning: we paid to have a terrace, but there were no cushions on the chairs, so we got little use of the feature.

The staff are amazing! I asked my teenagers what they will miss about Paris...."Mom the people at our hotel are sooo nice." That says something. Great location, you can literally walk everywhere (except Versailles LOL!) Lots of cafes and shops on the same street. Got HUGE bottles of water at the little bodega 3 shops down. A fromagerie also, 2 shops down next to the Louvre Wine Museum and shop. Nickola our bartender for happy hour has become a part of our family! The rooms and bathrooms are huge and super comfortable by European standards. The A/C was great! Loved our stay!!!

Located on a side street near the Louvre, the hotel is walking distance from Chatelet des Halles, the Marais and the Left Bank. The room was huge and clean and the staff friendly and helpful, especially the woman who mans the desk during the day - thanks for the great recommendation for a local restaurant we never would have found otherwise. Nice breakfast too!

L'empire was my home base for 9 days in Paris. I was very pleased that the room and bath were appreciably larger than most Paris hotels on my past trips. The staff, particularly the evening and overnight crew, were very friendly and helpful.

The location is perfect, 5-10 minutes from the Louvre and the Seine, 1 minute to the Metro. Breakfast was good, the bed wonderful, and the WiFi excellent.

The only minor criticism is the lack of English language TV channels. Nothing from America to keep up with the news.

This is a Fantastic property. The room was spacious, clean and quiet. It is close to the Louvre and the Metro is a 3 minute walk. The staff was excellent. They were friendly and helpful. They answered any questions and helped with directions.

We found L’empire to have great location, service and spacious rooms. Clean and practical. Decor could be improved, however the hotel is totally worth it. We walked 4 minutes and we were at the Louvre.
We got a room with a nice view and a spacious bathroom. The breakfast was good as well.

Great location, spacious room, most comfortable hotel bed I ever slept in(and I traveled a lot). The staff, every single one is extremely helpful and courteous especially Sonia, she understands exactly what each guests needs as a tourist or otherwise. She is very knowledgeable and has a great sense of humor. Rooms didn't have much of a view and we didn't watch TV because everything was in french but then it's Paris you want to be enjoying the city & come to room to rest & refresh and it sure is perfect for that.
I will be recommending this place to all my friends and will definitely stay there when I visit again.

We had a wonderful stay at L'Empire Paris. The staff was super helpful and welcoming, and the location is excellent. You have Seine, Louvre close by and Place de le Concorde, Champs-Élysées, Arc de l’triumph and the Eiffel Tower are all within walking distance.

You have 3 metro stations nearby and RER train at Les Halles (directly to the airport)

I would recommend this hotel for you next trip to Paris

We had a wonderful stay at L'Empire Paris. The staff was super helpful and welcoming, and the location couldn't be beat for strolls along the Seine - Pont Neuf is just a 5 minute walk away, and the Louvre is nearby as well. Plus, the room was huge for Europe and was quiet (no street noise or noise from nearby rooms). We got the best sleep! Awesome hotel all around!

Our family had a great three night stay in L'Empire Hotel in Paris last week. This hotel is within walking distance of the Louvre and three Metro stations and is an ideal location for exploring Paris. All the staff spoke excellent English and were courteous and friendly. The breakfast was superb and I would highly recommend this hotel for a stay in Paris.

L’Empire is a great friendly, perfectly located hotel for touring the famous Paris landmarks. The Louvre, Place de le Concorde, Champs-Élysées, Arc de l’triumph and the Eiffel Tower are all walkable. Also the Seine is a 3 minute walk away.
Hotel is very comfortable and clean, staff very friendly and helpful. More than adequate buffet breakfast.
Cafés and restaurants are plentiful and close to the hotel.

We had the most wonderful time at L'Empire Paris. We stayed here the last few days of our trip to France. The rooms were spacious, and accommodations were above expectations. From beginning to end the staff was helpful and courteous. They had no-issue with our broken French and spoke English very well.

The location is near the Louve and a great location for walking/exploring, shopping, restaurants, or late-night cocktails.

What an excellent location to spend the end of our time in France.

We just completed a two night stay at L’Empire Hotel. This is my “ go to “ hotel in Paris .. the staff is very courteous and helpful, the rooms are comfortable and well equipped, beds and linens just what I like.. the location is perfect.. I always use the RER from CDG for 10 e one way.. arriving at Les Halle station, it is only 5 minute walk.. no changing trains or walking far with luggage. The area that has been under construction for quite some time is finished.. the new Samaritan is beautiful .. the Louis Vuitton building, including museum , is right next door. From L ‘Empire The Pont Neuf bridge is a quick walk to cross the Seine.. and The Marais is a short walk heading east. Westbound is the Louvre. Great restaurants, Patisserie and Pharmacie. Yesterday we scheduled a covaid test at the Pharmacie around the corner for returning to the US today.. perfect !
L’Empire is part of the IPrefer boutique hotel group. I like hotels in this group so I’m building points here and book direct. The staff, when able, will upgrade me ,which I greatly appreciate.

This is a "boutique" hotel with numerous amenities. The morning always started off well with the continental breakfast and fresh coffee offered. The staff was very courteous and professional. The rooms were small, clean, and comfortable. Paris is a walking town. The hotel is located in a beautiful area between Rue de Rivoli and Rue de Saint Honore, and close to many attractions, the Louvre, La Seine, and Tuillerie Gardens were very close. When we return to Paris, we will make a point to have reservations at L'Empire.

First time in Paris staying here and we are glad we chose this hotel. The location is great, a short walk to the Louvre and Notre Dame. Lots of shops and amenities nearby and transportation to other Paris sights was easy.
The staff were welcoming and friendly and spoke English which made our stay a lot easier as our French is minimal. Our room was clean, spacious and well equipped.

Good experience but one bad point is that you must not rely on the Hotel's services and this is a shame:
- no in-room meal services by the hotel on a Saturday night
-I forgot my toothbrush and toothpaste and the hotel does not have any kit for a 4 star hotel.

so I am very disappointed even if the room is great.

My wife and I visited Paris in October 2021 to celebrate our wedding anniversary. We booked this hotel having a perfect location in central Paris (arrondissement #1). The hotel is a four star but the quality of service we received is a well deserved five star and facility cleanliness was always perfect. Next time we fly to Paris, we dont look any other place than this one perfect hotel. Breakfast included was fresh with a good choice. The only missing part was restaurant was not opened for dinner but there is a large variety of good restaurants all around.

I have been traveling worldwide for more than 20 years. In this hotel, I experienced terrible experiences.

Pipe was broken and huge water falling from the ceiling while I laying on the bed!!

It potentially could cause electricity short then kill me.

Hotel staffs helped me to change a better room but this hotel exists a safety concern which should be the basic requirement of a 4 star hotel.

Even safe Box in the room was broken!! I called hotel service 3 times but it still not working!! I do worry about where and how to secure my passport and cash .

Overall speaking, facilities are too old in this hotel.

I think I shall never come back this one since there are many other better choices in surrounding area.

You get no value for your money.
We were so disappoint about the room at the hotel - we got a roof room so pore - the bed was really hard and bad.
There was no coffee machine as in promises.
Dark room - the desk was under the window, so you could not use.
This is not a 4 star hotel - maximum 3, because off the lokation and the breakfast
I'll travel a lot in Paris, so know the standard on the hotels.
No value for money

This hotel was just perfect for me. The location can’t be beat- steps from the Louvre and within distance to so many things and close to the metro (the Louvre and Les Halles stops, which also makes it very easy to get to from the airport). The rooms are very clean and well equipped. I was lucky to get a room upgrade to a very spacious room with a terrace but I don’t doubt the other rooms would be great too. The shower pressure was so good. The staff was fantastic- very friendly and knowledgeable. I will definitely stay here again the next time I’m in Paris.

A stone's throw from the Louvre and walking distance from major sights.
Staff really friendly and helpful
Nice clean room although walls paper thin so we could hear people coming in and out of rooms.
Definitely recommend and would stay here again.

Friendly staff. Got an extra big room with lot of space (and bathtub!) which was perfect since we were staying almost a week. The breakfast was included which we found out as a great surprise since we really appreciated it. The breakfast was pretty small but had everything you need, we also liked the fact that the bread and juices etc was served by the table.
It’s clear that the hotel has been doing a few years already and they could make it more clean but overall we are happy with our staying.
Best of all tho was the area which really suited us, compared to all the areas we visited we found the best shopping and absolutely best restaurants and cafes just around the corner with less tourists than downtown.

Excellent boutique hotel in a perfect central location. The room with terrace and jacuzzi was spacious and well appointed. Staff at reception was very welcoming and friendly. Location is outstanding - we walked to pretty much every landmark in Pari without having to rely on public transport. There are many great restaurants around … Would highly recommend L’Empire and we will likely come back!

L’Empire is a great find for a small piece of luxury in a large city that does not break the bank. A 4-Star hotel with all the expected amenities, cleanliness, and comfort that you would expect.

Upon arrival at the hotel, located only a short 5-10 minute walk from Les Halles metro station, we were greeted by a friendly and pleasant front desk manager, who kindly upgraded our room to an executive room, this was a nice touch and gratefully received.

The hotel located in a very central location and within easy accessible reach of all tourist landmarks of Paris, and only 40 mins away from Disneyland Paris via (RER C train line).

The hotel reception lead to a small but pleasant resident lounge, adjacent was the bar and dining area. The areas being of clean nature and to a good specification along with mood lighting, this very pleasant in the evening and very quite and calm ambiance, most welcoming after a long day in Paris & Disneyland.

Our room allocated as an upgrade was located on the 5th floor, although the single lift was quite slow in arriving, it was a pleasant welcoming once we arrived at the room.

Initial impressions were great, a very spacious room with great decoration. Separated into three areas, the bedroom, the lounge, along with the bathroom.

The bedroom was extremely spacious with a high headboard and great pattern and colours, a large side desk made from laminated shattered glass which was very effective. The wardrobe was however located within the lounge strangely, although was not a problem.
The only thing, was that there was no bedside draws but shelfs, so nowhere to place underwear, again except for a large draw within the lounge. Also a large TV with sound bar.

The lounge again very spacious and a long glass sideboard, TV / Sound bar, large sofa and along with mini bar (chargeable) and coffee maker. Very homely with coffee table and soft furnishings.

The Bathroom had modern twin sinks and a water jet bath. All extremely clean, just a bit of limescale on the show seal.

All in all this hotel was a great location, friendly staff, modern, comfortable and luxurious features. A hotel that I would stay at again time and time again.

The front desk always made it their job to ensure that we were okay, great recommendations of the local area, and great engagement with kids!

Well done L’Empire and thank you to all the staff that made us welcome and pleasant stay.

My family and I were guests for 10 days at Hotel L'Empire Paris. Regrettably, our experience with this hotel isn't a positive one. This is because we were given two rooms in the basement on floor level -1. Because of this location, we did not get a good value for our money and did not have a good experience.

On this floor, the corridor is in complete darkness (lights set on a timer), except when you walk out of the elevator the lights go on only for about 5 seconds. So if you did not reach your room in time, the lights go off and you can not see where to stick the entry card into the door, you have to walk back towards the elevator so the light sensors would turn the lights back on. On all the other floors, the corridor lights are on all the time. There is a smell emanating from the adjacent spa, and there are fowl body odors from the cleaners if you enter the rooms right after the cleaning was done. The rooms overlook a small interior courtyard, not a great view.

It is possible that the review would have been different if we stayed on the upper floors. If you plan on staying at this hotel, make sure you are not assigned to a room in the basement. Do it as a condition of your booking.

First, I have to say thank you to the staff. I booked a non refundable rate in January 2019 for April 2019...they gave me a credit and extended it twice so we were actually able to stay.
If you are looking for a great location in Paris this is it. Plenty of shops and restaurants but not too touristy. It is close to the metro, the Lourve, and easy to walk to the beautiful park nearby. The room was quiet and away from the road. The bed was more comfortable than mine at home. The staff is lovely and kind. Definitely a great place to stay and I can't thank them enough.

The staff at L’Empire was fantastic!! Check in was great especially after a long flight. We also received great restaurant recommendations! Would definitely stay here again and would recommend it to anyone! The location is perfect for walking/training around Paris. Close to great restaurants and boulangeries as well.

We were overall very pleased by our stay at L'Empire. The staff was polite and helpful. The rooms were comfortable. And the best part of this hotel is its proximity to the Louvre and the Louvre-Rivoli metro station. I would stay here again, especially if the prices remain as affordable as they were. Not a lot of frills and extras, but it had everything we needed for a week's stay.

The only negative experience we had was ordering Room Service. They advertise the brand, but I didn't realize that the room service would be a microwavable meal. I was very disappointed. It was our second most expensive dinner in Paris and by far the absolute worst. I had assumed the food was prepared in a kitchen on site, but it's not. I did look it up, and saw that this particular company is popular in France, so I could be the problem, but after a week of eating fresh, delicious meals in the plethora of restaurants that surround this hotel, the room service stood out as particularly offensive.

But if you just don't order room service, I believe you'll have a very enjoyable stay at this hotel.

From the first time we walked into the place we were pleased. Front desk staff was very friendly and helpful to 2 confused Americans who had just wandered out of the train station. The rooms were thoroughly cleaned daily. The wine at the bar was inexpensive and quite good. Ricky at the bar knows the area so well and will recommend for you any restaurant that you would like. He led us to our second favorite restaurant in Paris which we would have never found without him. All in all, based on the location, cleanliness, and friendliness of L'Empire, I would honestly give perfect marks for all with not even the slightest criticism.

I booked a room for 9 days about 30 or so days before we travelled to Paris. I booked this hotel not really knowing much about it but after a little research I am so glad that I booked it! From the check in process to the desk staff and the daily housekeeping services, this was probably one of the best choices; and talk about convenient! One train from De Galle (RER B) and a short 10 minute walk and everything you need is within steps of the hotel. I HIGHLY recommend this hotel and will definitely stay here on my next excursion to Paris!

Loved this hotel ! Sonia welcomed us when we arrived and from that moment we knew we found the perfect hotel. She was friendly, funny and helped with all of our needs . Ricky made us so wonderful drinks and provided several recommendations for dinner that did not disappoint. My son lives only 2 hrs away from Paris and he said he will definitely stay here on return visits. Rooms as spacious and the hotel is in a perfect location. I can’t wait to come back

From the moment we arrived we felt extremely welcome! Sonia at the front desk was so friendly as was Ricky, the concierge.

My sister and I reserved a room with two twin beds and it turned out to be an upgraded room on the 6th floor. It was so roomy and comfortable!

The neighborhood was exceptional, with plenty of bistros and shopping!

Next time we find ourselves in Paris we will definitely stay at L’Empire again!

Liz and I really enjoyed our stay at L’Empire. The hotel is situated in a great location and our room was very comfortable. The staff are really friendly and helpful, always providing very useful help with directions and restaurant bookings/recommendations.
Strongly recommended

Young, friendly staff who helped us tremendously in our two week stay. I recommend the room with the jacuzzi as well. Truly relaxing. Martin and I hadn't had a vacation in 20 months due to Covid. It was the perfect place to reconnect. Be aware that the demonstrators are nearby on Saturdays so don't plan to arrive nor depart on that day. One couple had to walk from the Gare de Nord due to no taxis. They wheeled their luggage here. BBC on TV but took a break from CNN. Loved the subtitles on Channel 15; I learned some French. The breakfast staff - very sweet people who learn how you want your coffee. Emma at front desk - superbe and so is Ricky. We are returning in November.

Check in was a breeze and the front desk staff was great. They provided directions and recommendations for dinner. The room was clean and very nice with a balcony type window overlooking the street. Even with the proximity to the street, when the window was fully closed it was nice and quiet. Breakfast was a nice continental breakfast ( limited due to Covid, but still available). Ricky was extremely helpful and greeted us every afternoon. The location was great and i would stay here again.

room was great, calm, clean, very comfortable. breakfast was ok since we are in France. The people were friendly and helpfull. I recommand this hotel and I will come back with my wife.in the middle of a lot of places to see: bourse, samaritaine, beaubourg, les halles

Really nice location. Walking distance to the Lourve. Really close to a Metro stop. Lots of great restaurants within walking distance (really enjoyed The Plume!).

The rooms were nice, quiet, clean, and adequately equipped. Complementary breakfast was always the same and of limited selection. It was good, though after several days of the same thing, it did get a repetitive.

One of the best things about the hotel was the staff. Their staff is GREAT! Everyone we encountered was helpful. Honorable mentions go to a few in particular. Emma was the first person we met when we went to check in and she was a real gem. I found her to be very helpful and conscientious. She's a great "first impression" and she's a true professional who assisted us throughout our stay.

Ricky (night manager??) was REALLY helpful , too. He was always willing to help out however he could. Emma was another great employee who helped out whenever she was on.

The ONE thing that was frustrating for us was that our electronic keys kept failing. It didn't matter where we carried them (wallets, pockets, purse, etc.) or left them in the room. We had to have all 3 of them reactivated a number of times. I don't know if it's how they're programed, or if they're just a really bad batch of cards. But, they were a pain to deal with. Fortunately, we were close enough to the front desk that it was easy enough to just go up and have them reactivated. Not fun if there was a line or even less if we'd been on a different floor. Hopefully, that's something that gets fixed.

L'Empire is a smaller boutique hotel in the 1st Arrondissment. It is very near Pont Neuf and the Louvre/ Rivoli Metro stop. Almost everything is within walking distance. The room was very spacious and clean. The breakfast was included in our room type and was very complete with excellent service. All that being said, the hotel staff was extraordinary, the kind of service only found in the most exclusive hotels. One example, of the many, was one hotel staff member not only gave us directions to the Metro stop, but also took us to the point where we could see it. The staff was also very cordial and made you feel like you were the only guest in the hotel. We want to thank all the staff members for their professionalism and especially to Sonia for her expertise and knowledge of Paris to make our trip truly incredible including getting us a last-minute driver to take us to the airport.

We stayed here for a few days following a conference. We had chosen to extend our stay for a few days and found L’Empire from a quick search.

It’s rare that I’m willing to write reviews, but I felt compelled to given the incredible service, quality of the facilities, and experience we had at L’Empire. From the moment we arrived, the front desk agents (all of whom are hilariously and are almost aggressively complimentary) are some of the best I’ve interacted with in the world.

We had a single room for one person and a double that was upgraded to a triple with larger room and a terrace on arrival. Both rooms were great, but the triple with the terrace was really great as it give a sense of intimacy and “belonging” as though you had your own little slice of Paris to enjoy like a local.

The location is also excellent and centrally located to everything. We didn’t have a chance to try the cafe downstairs as we were busy with local friends or peers, but things looked great there too. Cannot recommend the Empire enough and will likely be staying whenever I need a hotel in the area.

Staff is extremely welcoming and make you feel like home. Room is big enough for a couple with luggage. While our stay there, all the staff was really helping, like Ricky. The hotel is located the center of Paris, the famous attraction is only steps away, and metro station is also not far so it’s very easy to connect you to the rest part of the city. Highly recommended.

This is a nice hotel with a perfect location, at walking distance from the Louvre. The staff is extremely kind and helpful. We chose breakfast included and would highly recommend it. Our stay was very pleasant during those 5 days in beautiful Paris.

My husband and I traveled with our 12 year old daughter and hotel was purely amazing. Great location, within walking distance to Louvre, restaurants, shops and metro. Everyone was so helpful and polite. We truly appreciated the kind service and guidance.

Unique looking hotel right in the middle of a quaint city neighborhood. Plenty of food options near by, a quick walk to the louvre and all things surrounding that. Lewis at the front desk was wonderful. His English was great which was helpful when we were missing a couple things in our room. He brought them up right away with a smile. He was very kind and helpful, especially when our French is extremely limited.

We staid 2 nights in hotel.
Everything was very good, we’ll return here.
We liked hotel, room was ok. Also liked very much location, for both day-life and night-life.
Also hotel staff was very friendly, they helped us when need.

Clean, friendly and professional staff, also convenient location next to Louvre and other attractions. Family rooms available king and queen sofa bed were comfortable for this two adult and two kids family. Thank you Ricky and team.

Great hotel. Rooms were clean, beds were good, and a very spacious bathroom. The location is great, just 5 mins walk to Louvre Museum, metro station also nearby. But most of all the staff was fantastic. They were really helpful and friendly. They will help you with anything!

Superb! I spent 2 wonderful nights at the Empire (8-10 June), the staff couldn’t have been more welcoming, courteous and professional. The hotel is minutes away from Le Louvre, in a surprisingly quiet street. My room (De Luxe 203) was very large by Parisian standards with a massive, super confortable bed and a huge bathroom (complete with bath and two sinks) Superb location, superb staff, superb value for money - I will definitely book again!

Wonderful hotel with a great and outgoing staff. You could not ask for a better location to launch your exploration of Paris. 3 minutes away from The Louvre in the heart of shopping and dining. The staff is friendly and welcoming, and will do their best to help you in any way.
